<HEAD>Risque Business? Playboy Hops Over Remnants of Iron Curtain</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ALEX BANDY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Playboy of the Western world arrived in the the <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> bloc today, unveiling <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> women to a nation more concerned with shedding Communism. A Hungarian version of the men's magazine hit the stands today. Playboy debuted the edition Wednesday at a news conference that was the best attended since President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> visited <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION> in July. The star attraction was December's Playmate of the Month, American <PERSON> Pia </PERSON> <PERSON> Reyes </PERSON>, who told reporters she hoped she is `` recognized with clothes on.'' <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION> apparently was chosen for the first East Bloc edition because of its liberal cultural and political climate. This year, the <ORGANIZATION> Communist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> disbanded and reform-minded leaders have promised free elections by June. In the maiden Hungarian edition, <ORGANIZATION> Playboy </ORGANIZATION> founder <PERSON> Hugh </PERSON> <PERSON> Hefner </PERSON> wrote, `` The Hungarian people can now enjoy the same democratic freedom which <ORGANIZATION> Playboy </ORGANIZATION> has always championed.'' Playboy, however, is n't likely to shock Hungarians the way it did Americans in the 1950s. The past year has seen a rash of soft-core pornography appearing at <LOCATION> Budapest </LOCATION> kiosks. There are no pornography statutes on the books in <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION>, but customs officials did routinely confiscate such magazines until 1983. The Hungarian edition of <ORGANIZATION> Playboy </ORGANIZATION> will have an initial printing of 95,000 copies and will sell for 197 forints, or about $ 3, a steep price in a country where the average monthly salary is about 6,000 forints, or $ 100. The <ORGANIZATION> Hungarian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Playboy </ORGANIZATION>, a joint venture between <ORGANIZATION> Playboy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Enterprises </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZ