ausen </PERSON>'s armored limousine into a heap of twisted metal and blew out windows in buildings His driver, <PERSON> Jakob </PERSON> <PERSON> Nix </PERSON>, was seriously injured, but police said his condition was not critical. Security agents following in another car were unhurt. A letter found at the scene claimed responsibility on behalf of the <ORGANIZATION> Red </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Faction </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>'s deadliest terrorist group, of which little had been heard since 1986. <PERSON> Foerster </PERSON> said the letter `` was not typical'' of <ORGANIZATION> Red </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Faction </ORGANIZATION> claims because it did not explain motives. After previous attacks, the terrorist group left lengthy statements giving detailed reasons for the actions. He said the letter was signed `` Commando <PERSON> Wolfgang </PERSON> <PERSON> Beer </PERSON>,'' for a suspect in an investigation of the <ORGANIZATION> Red </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Faction </ORGANIZATION>, and carried Faction symbols: a star-shaped symbol and a drawing of a Kalashnikov assault rifle. Interior Minister <PERSON> Wolfgang </PERSON> <PERSON> Schaeuble </PERSON>, who is in charge of police and security issues, said protection for prominent figures was stepped up after a <ORGANIZATION> Red </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Faction </ORGANIZATION> hunger strike that ended last April. During the fast, one imprisoned terrorist called for increasing activities `` with all means.'' <PERSON> Schaeuble </PERSON> told <ORGANIZATION> ZDF </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> TV </ORGANIZATION> that since then, <ORGANIZATION> Red </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Faction </ORGANIZATION> followers are believed operating with more autonomy than before, when th