 The Sandinista-dominated <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assembly </ORGANIZATION> voted Thursday to strip opposition candidate <PERSON> Virgilio </PERSON> <PERSON> Godoy </PERSON> of his immunity from prosecution as a deputy, opening the way for possible charges of mismanagement. Even before the vote, <PERSON> Godoy </PERSON> scoffed at the procedure. He called it part of a leftist <ORGANIZATION> Sandinista </ORGANIZATION> plot to discredit him as vice presidential candidate of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Opposition </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> and weaken the anti-government bloc. The 14-party bloc is the major rival of the ruling <ORGANIZATION> Sandinista </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION> in Feb. 25 elections. `` What they have done today is a farce, and farces are performed by humbugs,'' <PERSON> Godoy </PERSON> said after the vote, which he boycotted. Sandinistas hold 61 of the 96 seats in the single-house legislature. Deputies from six opposition parties hold the remaining 35 seats. <PERSON> Godoy </PERSON> is president of the <ORGANIZATION> Liberal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Independent </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> and one of its nine deputies in the assembly. The measure to strip him of his parliamentary immunity passed 61-1, with one abstention. A Conservative Democrat Party deputy voted against. A deputy belonging to a Liberal faction opposed to <PERSON> Godoy </PERSON> abstained. Thirty-three deputies were absent, including 21 opposition deputies. Accusations focus on items and about $ 60,000 donated to a Godoy-directed research center by the <ORGANIZATION> Friedrich-Naumann </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foundation </ORGANIZATION>, based in <LOCATION> Bonn </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>. The foundation said it was satisfied with how its donations were managed and called questions about the management `` baseless.'' <PERSON> Godoy </PERSON> says members of a rival <ORGANIZATION> Liberal </ORGANIZATION> faction who questioned the center's handling of donations were put up to it by the <ORGANIZATION> Sandinistas </ORGANIZATION>.
