ired to have, among other things, better shielding around the gas tank. <LOCATION> Louisville </LOCATION> surgeon Dr. <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Malangoni </PERSON> testified that six of the survivors he treated would have died of suffocation if they had n't received prompt medical attention He also described amputating the severely burned foot of Miss Aurentz, who suffered burns over 55 to 60 percent of her body and has required extensive surgery. <PERSON> Mahoney </PERSON> is charged with 27 counts of murder, 42 counts of wanton endangerment, 12 counts of assault and one count of drunken driving. Testimony is expected to move onto the 27 murder counts next week, but <PERSON> Richwalksy </PERSON> declined to say when that phase of the trial would begin.
