<HEAD>Third Man Sentenced in Ethiopian's Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The third man charged in the racially motivated beating death of an Ethiopian student has been sentenced to 20 years in prison. <PERSON> Steven </PERSON> <PERSON> Strasser </PERSON> had pleaded guilty to first-degree manslaughter in the Nov. 13, 1988, slaying of 27-year-old <PERSON> Mulugeta </PERSON> <PERSON> Seraw </PERSON>. <PERSON> Strasser </PERSON> asked for leniency before sentencing Wednesday but <ORGANIZATION> Multnomah </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Circuit </ORGANIZATION> Judge <PERSON> Philip </PERSON> <PERSON> T. </PERSON> <PERSON> Abraham </PERSON> called the death a `` shocking and horrendous crime.'' `` I'll never again be a part of a group that advocates violence,'' <PERSON> Strasser </PERSON> said in a statement to the judge. But <PERSON> Strasser </PERSON> stopped short of denying that he harbored racist views when questioned by <PERSON> Abraham </PERSON>. <PERSON> Abraham </PERSON> read from a report by a psychologist who concluded after interviewing <PERSON> Strasser </PERSON> that he `` felt pride in the concept of the white working man but that he did not have extreme racial views.'' When <PERSON> Abraham </PERSON> asked if that was how he felt, <PERSON> Strasser </PERSON> replied: `` I did n't necessarily say that. I think people should have a right to belong to a group.'' <PERSON> Strasser </PERSON>, 21, was a member of <ORGANIZATION> East </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Side </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pride </ORGANIZATION>, a group advocating white supremacy. Two other members of the same group, <PERSON> Kenneth </PERSON> <PERSON> Mieske </PERSON> and <PERSON> Kyle </PERSON> <PERSON> Brewster </PERSON>, pleaded guilty to murder and manslaughter, respectively, in <PERSON> Seraw </PERSON>'s death. <PERSON> Strasser </PERSON> joined White Pride `` partially out of loneliness and wanting to belong to a group,'' said his attorney, <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Haslett </PERSON>. `` He is just a nice young boy whose life is ruined.'' Besides manslaughter, <PERSON> Strasser </PERSON> also pleaded guilty to second-degree assault for striking another victim. He pleaded no contest to a charge of racial intimidation arising from the same incident.
