<SECOND>BC-Disabilities Act, Adv 03-1st Add,0201</SECOND>
<HEAD>$adv03</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Sunday, Dec. 3, and thereafter</HEAD>
<HEAD>WASHN: Rudman says.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 The bill includes assorted timetables and exemptions: _ Businesses with fewer than 25 employees are exempt from the employment provisions for the first two years After that, those with fewer than 15 employees are exempt. Public accommodations provisions take effect 18 months after enactment. _ Smaller and shorter buildings are exempt from special elevator requirements, but no exception is made for shopping malls or medical offices _ All new public-transit vehicles must be accessible but those already on the road need not be retrofitted _ Private bus companies would have six to seven years, depending on their size, to begin buying new buses that are accessible to the disabled Since all buses last 10 to 12 years, the full conversion of the fleet would be gradual. _ Homosexuality, bisexuality, sexual behavior disorders are excluded from the definition of disability, as are compulsive gambling, pyromania, kleptomania and some other aberrations _ No punitive damages may be collected for violations However, fines of up to $ 50,000 for the first violation and $ 100,000 for subsequent violations may be imposed under the accommodations provision.
</TEXT>
